Package org.jcvi.jillion.core.datastore

The DataStore package deals with classes that represent a repository of entities.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DataStore<T>
    A DataStore is an interface which represents a repository of entity records which can be fetched by a unique (to this DataStore) id.
    DataStoreFilter
    DataStoreFilter is a filter that can be applied to a DataStore to only allow certain Datastore ids.
    DataStoreUtil.AdapterCallback<F,T>
    AdapterCallback is a callback method that can convert one type into another.
    DataStoreUtil.CacheableDataStore<T>
    CacheableDataStore is an interface that is used for Cached objects created by DataStoreUtil.createNewCachedDataStore(Class, DataStore, int).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DataStoreEntry<V>
    A DataStore entry (key-value pair).
    DataStoreFilters
    DataStoreFilters is a utility class that contains factory methods to create several different types of DataStoreFilter objects.
    DataStoreUtil
    Utility class containing static factory methods to adapt DataStores into another types of DataStores.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    DataStoreProviderHint
    DataStoreProviderHint describes implementation hints to help datastore factories return instances of datastore implementations for the desired scenario.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DataStoreClosedException
    DataStoreClosedException is a IllegalStateException that is thrown if an operation that requires the DataStore to be open is called on a closed DataStore.
    DataStoreException  

Package org.jcvi.jillion.core.datastore Description

The DataStore package deals with classes that represent a repository of entities.
